story.title: Suicide Angels - Episode 1
story.storyDescription: When seventeen-year-old Ella goes missing, her best friends begin to unravel the secrets of the night she disappeared…
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: Jennifer Park lives amid the bayous of Southeast Texas with her family. By day, she teaches middle school, and by night, she writes YA novels.

story.postPaywallNotification: OMG—why did the girls hear a door slam in Ella’s abandoned house? Tap into Hooked to find out 😱🔪

messages.text: Cass, tell Ella to text me back!
She’s not here.
Didn’t she go home with you last night?
She didn’t — she said she was going home with you…
Nope, Kinslee and I left together. She dropped me off.
You…you didn’t get Ella?
I didn’t know I was supposed to!
Didn’t she text you?
No, you?
No, not since before the party.
Then who the hell took her home?
A text comes in through on Peyton’s phone.
SOS
Ella?
What is it?
But Ella doesn’t answer, so Peyton texts Cassie again.
Cass, did you get that text?
From Ella? Yes. She said SOS…
Yeah, she said that to me too—
Does that mean what I think it means?
That she’s in trouble? Where is she?
Hang on, I’m gonna keep trying to text her again.
Kinslee enters the text chain.
Guys, did you get that text from Ella?
Yes.
She said SOS — but now she won’t respond to me. Didn’t she go home with Cassie?
Nope. And she’s not answering me either.
Check Snapchat. Maybe that will tell us where she is.
I am. Where are all her pics from last night?
She took like fifty of us. Did she delete them?
Her phone’s showing up at her house.
Maybe we should run over? Make sure she’s okay?
Yeah. We can find out who she went home with last night too.
Okay. Kinslee, can you come pick me up?
I’ll be over there in 10.
And I’ll meet you guys at Ella’s.
Twenty minutes later, the girls arrive at Ella’s house.
Looks like her mom’s car is here.
Her sister’s car, too.
Is that…is her front door open?
Hello? Ella?
Anybody home?
Are they here? I don’t hear anything…
I’m going inside. Come on.
Ella’s probably in her room upstairs.
The girls cross the threshold.
Guys, this feels wrong.
It’s not like we’re strangers, Kins. C’mon, it’s fine.
It feels…empty though. Like…
Abandoned.
Come on, why is the door open then?
They wouldn’t have just ran out the door and left it open, right?
You think something happened?
Ella wouldn’t have left her phone. It’s like, her appendage.
Kinslee, call it.
With a few clicks, Kinslee calls Ella’s phone. She holds her phone up to her ear.
I can hear it. I think it’s coming from her room.
The girls race up the stairs and swing open the door.
They stop, shocked at the chaos and mess.
What happened in here?
This room is always spotless.
Not anymore. Listen, where’s the phone?
Look! There it is — under the sheets.
Check her texts.
I am. Okay, here’s the one she sent us. But…
It says it was sent last night.
Then why did we get it today?
When did she send it?
After midnight.
Well, we left the party at eleven.
Any other texts?
The next is from a number — no name.
What does it say?
“Where are you?” It’s stamped ten-thirty.
That’s when she told me she was leaving with you.
Did the texter say anything else to her?
Nothing. It’s either the first text he sent—
Or Ella deleted the others before it.
Exactly.
We need to find out who that number belongs to.
Also, why did she send SOS?
And if her phone’s been here, why did it just come today?
The girls glance around the room.
Hey, what’s that on the bed?
Are those pills?
Peyton grabs the open bottle on the bed.
These are her mom’s painkillers from her knee surgery.
So why are they scattered all over the bed?
Guys, I just heard a door slam.
The girls look out into the hallway. A shadow moves inside one of the bedrooms.
Someone’s here.
Maybe it’s Ella.
They walk down to the last room and peer inside—
A young man is there, tearing through the drawers of Ella’s sister’s room.
Who the hell are you?
What are you doing here?
What are YOU doing here? That’s Ava’s room.
Is that Ella’s phone?
He lunges for it and begins scrolling through it frantically.
Hey, what are you—
Where is it? Where is the video? The photos…
Give it back. Ella will be pissed when I tell—
You don’t know?
The girls stare at him.
Shit, you really don’t know.
Know what? Where’s Ella?
Ella is…she’s dead.
Cassie gasps, and Kinslee and Peyton laugh with disbelief.
I think if our best friend were dead, we would know.
You’re crazy — or lying.
We were just with her last night.
But not for the whole night.
What are you talking about?
Wait, were you with Ella?
Hey, where are you going?
They follow him out of the house and stop when he gets in his car to leave.
Wait…I think I know him.
From where? Does he go to our school?
No, I’ve seen that car before. Look. He’s got a KA sticker.
Isn’t that your brother’s—
Yeah. It’s Ashton’s fraternity.
What was Ella doing with a frat boy?
And why was he looking for Ella’s phone?
Guys…
No. No, this can’t be true—
He’s lying.
Wait, guys, my dad is calling.
The girls stare down at Cassie’s phone. Peyton grabs Kinslee’s hand.
Cass, your Dad’s a cop. You think he knows something?
Answer it, Cassie.
But…
Just…just do it.
Cassie answers the phone. She listens in silence.
After what feels like an eternity, she speaks into the receiver.
Okay, I’ll be home soon.
When she looks up from the phone, she sees Kinslee studying her face urgently.
What did he say?
That it’s true—
Ella is dead.
